Subject: Fix find_available_evdi_device() to return the actual EVDI DRM card index

MrOz59-Apollo's find_available_evdi_device() incorrectly treats the return
value of evdi_add_device() as a device index. But libevdi's evdi_add_device()
writes "1" to /sys/devices/evdi/add and returns the number of bytes written
(1) on success, NOT the index of the newly created device. The new EVDI card
actually lands at whichever /dev/dri/cardN minor is free (e.g. card0 when the
dGPU is at card1).

Result without this patch: Apollo calls evdi_open(1) -> opens /dev/dri/card1
(usually the dGPU) -> returns NULL -> Apollo falls back to passthrough mode,
capturing the physical display instead of using a virtual one.

Fix: after add_device(), poll check_device(0..15) until one reports
EVDI_AVAILABLE, then return that real index. Handles udev's delay in creating
the new /dev/dri/cardN node.

Also requires that the calling user can write /sys/devices/evdi/{add,remove_all}
- see the evdi-perms.service systemd unit shipped alongside this package.

--- a/src/platform/linux/virtual_display.cpp
+++ b/src/platform/linux/virtual_display.cpp
@@ -334,20 +334,33 @@
   }
 
   static int find_available_evdi_device() {
-    // Find next available EVDI device
+    // First pass: any already-AVAILABLE EVDI device?
     for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
-      auto status = evdi.check_device(i);
-      if (status == EVDI_AVAILABLE) {
+      if (evdi.check_device(i) == EVDI_AVAILABLE) {
         return i;
-      } else if (status == EVDI_NOT_PRESENT) {
-        // Device doesn't exist yet, we can add it
-        int result = evdi.add_device();
-        if (result >= 0) {
-          BOOST_LOG(info) << "[VDISPLAY] Added new EVDI device: " << result;
-          return result;
+      }
+    }
+    // None available - add one. NOTE: evdi_add_device() returns the number of
+    // bytes written to /sys/devices/evdi/add (1 on success), NOT the device
+    // index. We must rescan check_device() to find which DRM minor the kernel
+    // assigned. Also gives udev a moment to create /dev/dri/cardN.
+    int added = evdi.add_device();
+    if (added < 1) {
+      BOOST_LOG(warning) << "[VDISPLAY] evdi_add_device() failed (returned " << added
+                         << "). Check that the user can write /sys/devices/evdi/add.";
+      return -1;
+    }
+    BOOST_LOG(info) << "[VDISPLAY] Added EVDI device; scanning for new index...";
+    for (int retry = 0; retry < 50; retry++) {
+      for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
+        if (evdi.check_device(i) == EVDI_AVAILABLE) {
+          BOOST_LOG(info) << "[VDISPLAY] New EVDI device available at index " << i;
+          return i;
         }
       }
+      usleep(50000);
     }
+    BOOST_LOG(warning) << "[VDISPLAY] Added EVDI device but no slot reported AVAILABLE after 2.5s";
     return -1;
   }
 
